Cell["\<\
The third dimension is used here just to \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]spice up\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] the chart, and the result is a plot that feels \
cluttered and is harder to read. This is just needless clutter, with no \
upside; don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t do this! Bar charts are intrinsically 2D \
objects, and you gain nothing by needlessly complicating them in this way.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787579201567774*^9, 3.787579284688086*^9}, {
  3.7875793231176357`*^9, 3.7875793410400553`*^9}, {3.7875793721217947`*^9, 
  3.7875793873597383`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9978c3d4-1012-4c5c-a88d-\
c2c1d8ba6f36"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Stacked bar charts", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787575947655087*^9, 
  3.78757595353576*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"84bf0a97-55b1-452c-b528-\
ca9d992af45b"],

Cell["\<\
Suppose we want to compare not only the total populations of countries, but \
also see how that population is divided between adults and children. What is \
the best way to plot that?

First, let us get the data.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787576471892352*^9, 
  3.787576581499324*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a7a11942-5230-4c63-8952-\
cdb087b17bb4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"popsAdult", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{"QuantityMagnitude", ",", "\n", "\t", 
     RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"CountryData", "[", 
         RowBox[{"#", ",", "\"\<AdultPopulation\>\""}], "]"}], "&"}], ",", 
       "\n", "\t", "countries"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"popsChildren", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"popsNow", " ", "-", " ", "popsAdult"}]}]}], "Code",
 InitializationCell->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787576584419846*^9, 3.787576584428149*^9}, {
   3.787576615627616*^9, 3.787576769508136*^9}, {3.787661193172525*^9, 
   3.787661230349154*^9}, 3.820319793621854*^9, {3.82032124015891*^9, 
   3.8203212415951033`*^9}, 3.8203389642656817`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[162]:=",ExpressionUUID->"bbb9b749-11a2-4742-b297-35a927723679"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "2.5502119`*^7", ",", "1.15993694`*^8", ",", "6.6489072`*^7", ",", 
   "2.1874725`*^7", ",", "9.315755`*^6"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8203894066860113`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[163]=",ExpressionUUID->"ce542a37-9c7d-4c2f-b9b6-ed06f1cf4d85"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["We could try to use the grouped bar chart, as before:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787576819683107*^9, 
