Cell["\<\
The logarithmic plot \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]unpacks\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
the points, and allows you to get a better view of how they are distributed.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787595793754676*^9, 3.7875958372138495`*^9}, {
   3.787595874388126*^9, 3.7875958750329595`*^9}, {3.7875961553089814`*^9, 
   3.787596199277012*^9}, {3.78759630660413*^9, 3.787596339743493*^9}, {
   3.787596378276331*^9, 3.787596397117603*^9}, 
   3.7875984503724575`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0c4dd5b1-977f-4639-84ab-\
5ffd59e3719c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Using functions to encapsulate and generalise useful plots", \
"Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787600784684221*^9, 3.787600818475629*^9}, {
  3.7876847144576006`*^9, 3.7876847146889815`*^9}, {3.7879754399060907`*^9, 
  3.7879754426117907`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"150ac8ac-c5f4-43af-925a-\
a413db9b0e89"],

Cell["\<\
What is we want to make a scatter plot of literacy versus mortality rate? or \
mortality rate versus inflation? It is very common when you are exploring \
data to want to plot many variations of the same kind of plot.

The way we created our scatter plot was very \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dirty\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]. We defined lots of little variables to hold the \
results of temporary computations, polluting the namespace, and we did lots \
of repetitive coding. To remind you:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7876008885094976`*^9, 3.7876009294200983`*^9}, {
  3.7876009862679653`*^9, 3.7876010303401117`*^9}, {3.7876011317729945`*^9, 
  3.787601166116184*^9}, {3.7876012065713573`*^9, 3.7876013794680796`*^9}, {
  3.7879757455164146`*^9, 
  3.787975748187049*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"313c20f6-f0da-4bbf-8ee5-\
050ce914cdcd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"countriesM", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"CountryData", "[", "\"\<Countries\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"literacy", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"CountryData", "[", 
       RowBox[{"#", ",", " ", "\"\<LiteracyFraction\>\""}], "]"}], "&"}], ",",
      " ", "countriesM"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"wealth", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"CountryData", "[", 
       RowBox[{"#", ",", " ", "\"\<GDPPerCapita\>\""}], "]"}], "&"}], ",", 
     " ", "countriesM"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Transpose", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"literacy", ",", "wealth"}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", "\n", "    ", 
   RowBox[{"AxesLabel", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<literacy\>\"", ",", "\"\<GDP per capita\>\""}], "}"}]}]}], 
  "]"}]}], "Code",
 InitializationCell->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787601393303056*^9, 3.7876013984752254`*^9}, {
   3.787601431586506*^9, 3.7876014572209263`*^9}, 3.7879757354543*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[179]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d518c043-4d64-4eb7-9c48-e77111263d2a"],

