Cell["\<\
Just by looking at this plot, we can tell that the population growth in these \
countries accelerated around the 1950s; that the US population has grown much \
more slowly than the other two; and that the growth of \
China\[CloseCurlyQuote]s population had a noticeable decrease in the mid-1990s.

Let us compare the wealth of these three countries:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7878392492358117`*^9, 3.787839427503683*^9}, 
   3.7878395066356764`*^9, {3.7878395772304254`*^9, 3.7878395788451924`*^9}, {
   3.787839704820883*^9, 
