Cell[TextData[{
 "Notice that the plot starts in 1960; earlier data is not available through ",
 StyleBox["CountryData",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The US\[CloseCurlyQuote]s wealth has increased steadily, particularly \
from the mid-1970s, while the other two countries seem to have stayed at low \
levels until the 2000s, when China\[CloseCurlyQuote]s wealth shoots up, and \
India\[CloseCurlyQuote]s increases as well. Notice the slump in the US\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s wealth, just before 2010. Any guesses about the cause of \
this?\n\nBecause of the tremendous disparity in the values, it is worth \
plotting this using a logarithmic scale for the vertical axis:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787839738413167*^9, 3.7878397658281884`*^9}, {
  3.787839867831319*^9, 3.78783994964219*^9}, {3.7878400139998736`*^9, 
