Cell["\<\
The changes become more clear, because the lines for India and China are not \
squashed by the presence of the much higher US values.

Another important point to consider when interpreting line plots is the data \
resolution. Let us plot the same wealth data, but at 5-year intervals:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7878409584551353`*^9, 3.787841021129538*^9}, {
  3.787841069719428*^9, 
  3.7878411536976104`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7bf94f31-8693-40be-a212-\
2ac89d173a82"],

