Cell["\<\
The slump in the US data all but disappeared! This is something to remember \
when interpreting your data using line plots.

If you have two different quantities changing over time (for example, \
population and wealth), laying two line plots vertically so that their axes \
are aligned is a good way to compare how the two quantities and see if their \
changes are related:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.787841200001836*^9, 3.7878412567993164`*^9}, {
  3.7878418072788954`*^9, 3.787841807435109*^9}, {3.7878421688953285`*^9, 
